{"id": "EUVD-2025-27917", "enisaUuid": "76193bf5-f97c-38f1-9887-64c4ab82f265", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nipv6: prevent infinite loop in rt6_nlmsg_size()\n\nWhile testing prior patch, I was able to trigger\nan infinite loop in rt6_nlmsg_size() in the following place:\n\nlist_for_each_entry_rcu(sibling, &f6i->fib6_siblings,\n\t\t\tfib6_siblings) {\n\trt6_nh_nlmsg_size(sibling->fib6_nh, &nexthop_len);\n}\n\nThis is because fib6_del_route() and fib6_add_rt2node()\nuses list_del_rcu(), which can confuse rcu readers,\nbecause they might no longer see the head of the list.\n\nRestart the loop if f6i->fib6_nsiblings is zero.", "datePublished": "2025-08-19T18:31:33", "dateUpdated": "2025-11-03T18:31:34", "baseScore": 0.0, "references": ["https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/6d345136c9b875f065d226908a29c25cdf9343f8", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/e1b7932af47f92432be8303d2439d1bf77b0be23", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/cd8d8bbd9ced4cc5d06d858f67d4aa87745e8f38", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/3c13db3e47e170bab19e574404e7b6be45ea873d", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/46aeb66e9e54ed0d56c18615e1c3dbd502b327ab", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/54e6fe9dd3b0e7c481c2228782c9494d653546da", "https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2025-38588", "https://lists.debian.org/debian-lts-announce/2025/10/msg00008.html"], "aliases": ["CVE-2025-38588"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.05, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "0780ac1b-2483-3322-8187-95313d848a16", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "6.13"}, {"id": "0d2c29c1-140d-36ab-82e8-36013199d294", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.17"}, {"id": "25692a5e-54f8-34fa-941b-9932a352f98a", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "d9ccb18f83ea2bb654289b6ecf014fd267cc988b <46aeb66e9e54ed0d56c18615e1c3dbd502b327ab"}, {"id": "36f63964-3d75-37d1-b7e7-3a9ba472ec5c", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "34a949e7a0869dfa31a40416d2a56973fae1807b 